>are viruses that will only infect thiles that contain large block of
0-bytes,
>start with a JMP instruction, are biggert (or smaller) than a particular

It is difficult to write a bait file that viruses will attach to.

8tunes refuse to infect anything smaller than 9K.
Zerohunt looks for an area of 0s in the file and plants the virus there. This
is Zero Hunts way of infecting files without an increase in file size.

This is why I use bait files from 2 bytes - 29696 bytes.

>Even if it does get infected, so what ?  If the virus is a stealth virus,
>the goat file will "look" the same as before infection.

If a stealth virus is suspected, or doesn't appear to infect any of my bait
files, I use my little .BAT file (published in Volume 6 issue 100) to see if
the virus is semi stealth, or fully stealthed, but doesn't restore the file
to it's original state. If this routine doesn't report anything, I cold boot
my test machine from a write protected bootable diskette.

